description: It's been two years since The War of Ghost ended, what's ace pilot Leila Stace to do now?
One man must fight to preserve the essence of life itself and protect the world around him. An action pack tale set in a tropical world of fantasy and splendor.

Circling the Triangle

H@TG continues its dizzying trip to the past as multiple time streams collide to prevent a future that cannot be avoided!
name: Circling the Triangle

description:
No Man's Land

The third riveting issue of the 8 part sci-fi graphic novel!

Part hard-boiled mystery, part sci-fi manga, and all out-of-this-world adventure

There's a bounty on Z's head. Unfortunately, every hunter in the sector is trying to collect. That means many of Z's friends have to decide just how much their friendship is worth. All Z can hope to do is survive, and find out just who is after him.
name: No Man's Land

description:
The Intern

Keira and Albert uncover the rogue mage Clious' nefarious plot and move to bring him down with a one-two magic punch of covert ops and tricky new spellcasting. But what's the deal with Clious' new apprentice and why-why-why are all the Quarra Witches attacking?! This is where it all ends- the grand finale of the first arc of everyone's favorite unpaid magic intern.
name: Chapter Six

description:
THE CASE OF THE IRON RAT

In this cyberpunk thriller, Animalia retreat into the virtual realm and ignore the real world as it slides further into decline. Among those users is Ram, a new breed of hacker seeking his fortune. Welcome to the wildlife that is METAZOA.
name: Book Three: The Case of the Iron Rat

description: On this episode of So You Think You're a Super Villain, Moon Streak starts his training regimen as Boaris and Rap Beat square off against one another and we find out what exactly is wrong with Mr. Collins.

The award-nominated UK superhero soap opera series continues!

One of the O Men's enemies has possessed Grace, and they've got very bad intentions. Get set for a special issue from the villain's point of view as 'Grace' joins The O Men on a mission in Brighton... Plus: prepare yourself for the latest shocking twist in the series!
Sulky, Mub and a bat are off to save Flags and another bat from The Horrendous' ominous town. Will they make it in time? Do they have to make it in time?
name: Chapter Seven

description:
Standard Foil

The continuing story of the Pizza Guy, a slacker prince in the early 90s, looking for love, and fighting corporate domination. Humor! Pathos! Philosophy! Slack!
name: Standard Foil

description:
"Kneading Dough" Part 3

What happens when Golden Megalopolis’s not so powerful superheroes join together to fight crime but they cannot even pay their own bills? Who’s going to put food on the table? How will they repair their costumes? Who’s going to pay for the damages? Would you like fries with that?

Diamond X was sneaking into Willie Johnson’s lab. What will become of Willie’s uncle and what secrets does he have to for Willie to fight the giant robot that is still terrorizing Golden Megalopolis!
name: Kneading Dough Part 3

description:
"Fowl Play" Part 1

In Poverty Thrill Adventures, find out the not so super secret origins of members of the ghettofabulous Poverty Pack!

Part One of the Fowl Play storyline. Bryce Bird pledges to fight crime and is mentored by his childhood heroes, Aphro Physt! But who is the villainous Le Courier and the Alabaster Association? Will Black Pigeon be able to bring them to justice?
name: Fowl Play Part 1

description: Things are exactly going well for Claire, but her sister Madison won't let her give up! Perhaps just one more try...
Red awakens to mysterious food as she recovers from her crossing of The Bone Tide. The Wolfe is visited by the Vulture and Robin, to disastrous result.
name: Blood & Feathers

description:
RubberMan Strikes Back

RubberMan gets into action! All-new chapter, all-new adventures!
name: RubberMan Strikes Back

description:
Salvation Chapter 2

Frank faces the blowback of his botched bust. Alonzo investigates a fresh killing. Oliver has a visitor, and the streets of Old Town aren't friendly to a lonely young lady.
name: Chapter Two

description: In a sense, despite turning the big 3-0, Ben Snakepit captures the same spirit in the comics he draws, summarizing each and every day of nearly the last decade of his life. In his second collection condensing the last three years, we see our hero move to and from Canada, tour the world with J Church, hang out with the Sainte Catherines, meet Mike Watt, get caught in the throes of whirlwind romances and we're there to watch helplessly as he gets his heart broken. There's also more pants-shitting, Adderall tripping and days of doing absolutely nothing to keep the old school fans happy. Also keeping with tradition there's a song allocated to each day and this collection comes with a mix cd of some of those songs for the maximum Snakepit life experience. Voted Best Minicomic - Wizard March 2006! Voted Best local comic - Austin Statesman 2006!
name: Volume 2: My Life In A Jugular Vein

description: Also contains 5 page preview of Long Live Pro Wrestling Comic series.

A hero never gets a break. As Ben mourns the death of his friends and tries to keep his own relationship under control, His life as SpeedStar quite literally "HEATS UP" as he comes across a new villain by the name of Mizz Leech, Whose powers mean there are now two speed demons in town!

The Trap: Chp 2

After being trapped inside the old farmhouse, the group of workers try to find a way out only to discover that there isn't one.
name: The Trap: Chp 2

description:
The Curse of the Black Fang

Police Detective Jon Feral wakes up bewildered,to a disturbing scene in an unfamiliar place. As he struggles to piece events together, Kristine converses with the M.E.G.A.S. about her own "rude awakening". Will she accept her responsibility and her new mentor's mystical training?
name: The Curse of the Black Fang

description:
Rebirth

Seventy five years ago Stardust the Super Wizard transformed Yew Bee into an abomination. Now that the Super Wizard has returned to the Earth the communist rat beast finally has his revenge.

But how will Yew Bee face off against Stardust's wife and elderly kid sidekick? And what has become of Stardust's intervention in Korea? And Violet McLane. How will she react to a monster who could kill a god?
name: Rebirth

description: Kite returns home to discuss an important decision with his family, while the tree witches arrive at their Gathering. There, two unusual guests take Sylvania in an exciting new direction.
Roxy attempts to clear the air with Beta, Gavin Wolf gains an ally and a refocused Binary sets their sights on a new target.
name: Chapter Four

description: Recent events in the city-state Terminus are drawing media attention. The city council is showing an increasingly less favourable attitude towards the future of the Project.

You've heard of alternate histories? Well Vikings vs. Unicorns is an alternate mythology, recasting everyone's favorite one-horned mythical icon of cuteness as a feral nightmare, endowed with immense powers and bent on destroying humanity. They are pitted against one of history's traditional villains, the Vikings, who are recast as humanity's grimly determined saviors. A whole lot of rainbow-colored blood is spattered across its opening pages and the fun just keeps raging on from there!

It's romance in the record business as Della discovers "No Man Can Thrill Me!" Then cowardly Dan Wilson juggles two women, weighing whether it's "Your Money, Or Your Love?" Remasters Young Romance #25 and #26, originally published in 1950.

Lost Attachments

Zombie Zero: Chapter 2 of 7

Alexander Livingston, the last Zombie, is on the loose. Dr. Victor Brooks finds a hired gun to recover his test subject.
name: Lost Attachments

description:
A life interrupted by destiny!

Antonio Valor's world...once commonplace and unsure...becomes clear and focused as he rises from the darkening depths of fear and doubt to the blinding illumination of understanding and strength.

Brotherman: Revelation...the first installment of the inception of Big City's mysterious purveyor of hope...of justice. The long awaited origin to ignite the senses and strike the imagination. A story that reaches back through the generations to set the foundation for the future.

Anyabwile, Sims, and McGee deliver the dynamic first part of a hero's saga...bursting with action, suspense, pain, and triumph.

The wait is over! The revelation is revealed.
name: Book One

description: A boy wakes up in the middle of the night by the mysterious sound of chains outside his window

Arctic Standoff / A Superpower Is Born

What better issue to kick-off the archives than the legendary Captain Canuck #1! Communist foreign agents commandeer an Arctic radar base and threaten Canada with a nuclear strike unless the country surrenders; Captain Canuck and his partner, Blue Fox, are sent to stop them.

All-new back story, "A Superpower is Born" written and drawn by Richard Comely himself!

Note: The digital edition (3/30/2016) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Arctic Standoff; A Superpower Is Born

description:
"They laid their hands upon the land as far as the circuit of the earth, their hearts confident and trusting: 'Our plans will succeed!'" Ramses III.

The Sea People bring fire and destruction during the bronze age to Egypt, Hatti, and especially to Canaan. But there is a prophecy about a child that will challenge them. A young boy with long hair that had never been cut...
Follow Kiko Nam as she battles the undead forces of evil through time! Collects the Tales of the Ex-Mortis stories "Camp Deserted" and "Say Your Prayers."

volume.name: Evil Dead 2: Tales of the Ex-Mortis: Kiko, Deadite Hunter Collection

description:
In 4000 B.C., the Sumerian city of Ahksa faces complete annihilation due to a severe and prolonged drought. To stem this tide, they have sacrificed one of their own every new season to a powerful demonic force that lives in a deep cavern nearby. A force that was originally summoned to protect them by using the Ex-Mortis. This remedy, however, has failed them over the last few years. Famine, starvation and death has engulfed the city. When Ishme the latest sacrifice, is thrown into the cavernous pit, he discovers the demon now wants something else. Does Ishme have what it takes to save his city?

Collects The Lottery Part One and Two from Evil Dead 2: Tales of the Ex-Mortis

volume.name: Evil Dead 2: Tales of the Ex-Mortis: The Lottery Collection

description:
University student Don Simmons sets on a dark path to the Ex-Mortis to win the love of a girl who doesn't notice him. As he encounters demons, terrorists, and rituals most foul, it's quite possible that Don is in way over his head.

Collects Soul Power Part One through Three from Evil Dead 2: Tales of the Ex-Mortis.

volume.name: Evil Dead 2: Tales of the Ex-Mortis: Soul Power Collection

description:
Brothers Beyond Blood

Taimur Malik, the country's best batsman at under-15 level, must put a lifetime's training to the test to live up to his father's reputation and break into the Pakistan Under-19 squad. But first he must compete against some of the country's most aggressive bowlers and skilled batsmen! Who will make it and whose best will simply not be good enough - find out in the action packed 'Khiladi' comic book series and enjoy the sport of cricket like never before!
name: Brothers Beyond Blood

description: When Major Sheffield Holmes, nephew to the great detective, and his mysterious American partner Capt. Imogen Watson solve a grisly murder in London's East End in 1914, they uncover a dark cabal that threatens to destroy the Holmes family and plunge the world into global war!
Family drama erupts for Maria as two estranged members resurface into her life. Pito gets a new pet, and Maria also starts a new job. Plus the legend of the MILVERINE.
Maria comes to terms with many estranged family relationships. Charlie gets kicked out of his studio apartment.

The Return of the King - Part 1

A small town finds itself in the path of a futuristic alien craft on a collision course with Earth. However, what's inside is neither alien nor from the future.
name: The Return of the King - Part 1

description: It's issue two of Susie Cagle's celebrated Food Not Bombs comic zine, 9 Gallons! This time around Susie addresses issues of volunteer burn-out, misguided agendas, and activist in-fighting. Hers is the story of San Francisco Food Not Bombs (specifically, for this issue, the underdoggy Civic Center lunch.) Over the course of 32 packed pages we get Susie dealing with her roommate just not gettin' it, fellow activists offering critiques but not solutions, and working hard with little help. But it's also fun-and funny-and Susie gives both a conversational insider look and a brief biographical sketch of the (non)organization. It's a struggle the whole way through while Susie looks for inspiration, answers, and hope, and runs up against nine thousand gallons of contradictory activist philosophy. An important moment (and message) comes late in the zine when Susie chats with a friend over email who tells her, "It's not about doing it, Susie. It's about doing it better." Part Food Not Bombs primer, part clear-headed look at volunteer ethics and philosophy, 9 Gallons' second issue is above all a great well-drawn story, a relevant discussion, and a thoroughly enjoyable read. Susie Cagle lives in Oakland and blogs regularly at thisiswhatconcernsme.com

Chapter 1

New York City, 2019. To protect Police Officers from the dangers of their job an elite law enforcement division, the Dead Division, staffed with weaponized remote controlled corpses and their operators has taken over most police functions in the city. The Dead Division reaches celebrity status with its huge success, but they have many dark secrets.
name: Chapter 1

volume.name: NYPDD: New York Police Dead Division

description: After trying to stay under the radar, Nous is loose and looking for revenge.

The First Collected Volume of the Weekly Action/Sci Anime Inspired Webcomic & Graphic Novel Series!

Awakening in the war ravaged era of Post Cataclysm Year: 693, an enigmatic and powerful young man known only as Rade finds himself lying face to face with a woman that has been brutally murdered.

With no recollection of his past or even his own name, Rade must quickly come to terms with the mysterious circumstances surrounding his memory loss and the peculiar woman's demise, as he is immediately thrust into a series of violent confrontations that will put his extraordinary abilities to the test.

As the saga of R:ILPERSONA begins to unfold, what will Rade find lurking beneath the mask of amnesia that conceals his true self: An innocent person, unwillingly thrown into a maelstrom of madness?

Or a monster, that...
name: Identity Negotiation

description:
The Enemy of my Enemy

Malik as he is chosen by the spirit of the earth, Gaea, to protect our world as a Shaman. But now, his quest has changed. Malik is being hunted and it's up to him to figure out who is trying to stop his quest and why. He will be confronted by perils from all sides and with the help of his rabbit mentor, Jeph, Gaea and an unlikely ally in a shape changer named Dominic, he will track down who is orchestrating this diabolical plan.
name: The Enemy of My Enemy

description: Stone + Wedge is the story of an Incan boy's encounter with extraterrestrials. The aliens have technology beyond the boy's comprehension, and are able to move boulders without breaking a sweat. The boy decides to steal the technology for his tribe, but at what cost? Ultimately, it's a story about perspective and why we shouldn't always fear the unknown.

Twenty-two artists explore what inspires them about the natural world, the plants and animals. For example:

Shashwat Mishra compares real dire wolves to the Game of Thrones version.

Steve Bissette wrote a story about his personal thoughts on the fisher cat, which was then illustrated by his hand-picked artist Ross Studlar.

Terri Nelson, who is preparing for a trip to the Antarctic, explains the purpose of museum collections not on display.

The Raw Deal

Col. Bird and his Mousse Intelligence Foods raid the Kitchen Weapons Lab in the first attack of their rebellion against the Cobb Salad Colonial Government. Empress Pineapple, O.R.G.A.N.I.C., General Gourd, and the Church of MochaTaco have other plans for the future of the table. The future appears to be in the hands of Mousse Intelligence Foods agents Black Ham and Hot Dog.
name: The Raw Deal

description: On the road again! Jimmy, Bones, Slim and Ralph Rojas take their band of Be-boppin' bugs on the road. Sparks fly at the Fox Theatre in Oaktown, where our boys luck their way into a wild jam session with the McKinley Blues Band, crossing Bop with the electric blues for a historic meeting of musical minds. Set in a 'bug noir' Manhattan of the nineteen-fifties, Bughouse weaves the story of an ensemble of characters who are essentially human beings with bug-like features, as they dance on the edge of the abyss. Steve Lafler brings alive a lost era of jazz and drugs that evokes a range of emotions and experience rarely seen in comic books.

Old Tales of Magic and Woe - Join Gene Luen Yang (Boxer & Saints), Nilah Magruder (M.F.K.), Carla Speed McNeil (Finder), Nick Dragotta (East of West), Nina Matsumoto (The Simpsons), Kel McDonald (Misfits of Avalon), Kate Ashwin (Widdershins), and more as they share with you tales of Asia!
name: Asia Edition

description: Heracles and Samson travel to the bustling city of Timnath, where a young Samson meets his first true love, Adriana! But some people are dangerous to love...
Now fairly comfortable with the language, Sister Long has more meaningful teaching experiences with the Japanese people than ever before. She and her friends celebrate a unique Christmas in Tokyo.
name: Month 11: December

volume.name: DENDO: One Year and One Half in Tokyo

description: Volume 3 collects issues #17–25, including the storylines "A Winter's Knight," "Landfall," and "Dragonring."
name: Volume 3

description:
Revelations

As Elizabeth and Julia are confronted by Gordon, Midnight finally meets Abigail who reveals Elizabeth's troubled past and brings into question if she truly is Junessa's saviour.
name: Revelations

description:
Oblivion

Abigail is bringing the final wave of monsters down on the survivors, who are still drunk and unequipped to fight. Hamilton is rallying whatever defence he can, but it seems the Gemini warriors are on their own against an army of 800 strong.
name: Oblivion

description:
Working Stiffs

Times are tough everywhere, even in the macabre town of Grimstone. With their house in a state of disrepair and their respective savings all but gone, Ribcage and company are forced to seek gainful employment. While most of them opt for the sensible and legitimate route, Count Cyanide has other ideas. What sort of twisted scheme has he concocted now?
name: Working Stiffs

description:
The Heart Man is a character born of Barbadian folklore. A forgotten terror that haunted the night in past decades has returned to Bayker's Ridge.

Fast forward to the year 2011, Bayker's Ridge has been transformed into urban developments and communities. The horrors of the past are awakened as we follow a group of young friends as they deal with the everyday trials of life; friendship, love, crime, drugs and now mysterious disappearances and killings in Bayker's Ridge.
name: Vol. 2

description:
Swing for the Fences

This is it! The final chapter of the first Hero Code arc!

Can our heroes stop the Mannequin in time to save the citizens of Halcyon City, or will they be undone before they have even begun?
name: Swing For the Fences

description:
Chapter II

In Chapter II, the adventure begins it's course with Peter, Bandit and Hank setting off into the wild to track down Pan and her captors. They weave their pioneering path into unfamiliar surroundings, both of nature and foe.
name: Chapter II

description: The Omni.
All of Hell's lords have fallen before Jesus, save one. Lucifer, the final adversary, is all that stands between Jesus and the end of his mission -- saving the souls of mankind.

Welcome to Barbados 2015, one of the world's prime tourist destinations, home of some of the best golf courses, casinos, luxurious night life and outrageous parties. Beautiful beach front properties and manmade islands add glitz and glamour.... but Barbados has dark side.

Everything seems to be getting back to normal on the home front. Dwayne has fallen into his role as Denise's protector and driver. With his dreams now dashed, Greg still hasn't abandoned the sport he loves. With Terrance assumed missing, and one of her good friends dead and the other seriously injured. Randy sets out on a personal mission of revenge. The lawmen Keith and Jason prepare for their next hit.

Certainly the head of a village known for throwing nightly parties and encouraging costumes will have all the answers... Right? June's quest to get back home brings her to seek an audience with Na-Rune-Tok Mair'alyn, where she makes new friends and becomes part of a ceremony that will change everything.

volume.name: The Lost Island of the Na-Rune-Tok

description:
Book of Lies

Who is behind the tragedy that occurred at Paradise High? Alex comes face to face with the culprit. Are they angel or human? Both? Neither? The answers will shake the foundations of both the Silver City and Los Angeles!
name: Paradise High Part Four of Five: Book of Lies

description:
The noise of thunder, part thirteen.

The Community told Tessa that the powers of Jill Kore and hers combined should connect Terra/Luna with Manifest. Now that the two women are together, will they be able to come back home?
name: The Noise of Thunder, Part Thirteen

description:
On the run

Before the "incident", Jack was just your regular Joe. One fateful day, some strange mysterious chemicals got all over Jack, which turned him into something else... As RubberMan Jack teamed up with local super heroine Awesome Gal for a while. But that attracted the attention of Don Melone who had plans in store for the town...
name: On the Run

description: This issue: an all-in, knock-down, drag-out family barbecue! The return of figures from both Shaman's and Zachary's pasts trigger some big conversations and revelations. Who is the mighty Gigaman? And whatever happened to the ORIGINAL Vanisher?

"The many-headed beast has but one true face. The face of corruption and unending thirst. A purge must be committed to cleanse all that would pollute. To cast to the unbreathable expanse the legacy of control. " Shepherd 12: 27-30

Slingers Two

Welcome to the Swinging Sixties...

A.D. 2963

SLINGERS is science-fiction adventure with a sixties aesthetic. The Rat Pack in space. DM and Frank are two wartime buddies now trying to make their way in a post-war world. DM is staying out of trouble for the sake of his fiancée, Jeannie, but Frank is finding it harder to stay on the straight and narrow. Despite their best intentions, they are about to be set on a new path where trouble finds them...

Follow Ben through his daily life illustrated as 3 comic panel adventures involving beer, weed, work, shows, tour, love, and parties filled with monsters. His drawing and writing style is sincere and heartfelt and you can imagine and feel his highs and lows. Each day is illustrated along with what he was listening to while drawing the frame. The quarterly and bi-monthly formats are no more, and now each year will be collected in a single slim paperback, just like in the beginning.
name: Volume 3: 2007

description: In the 2nd issue, Socute and Cassie spends the weekend at home having fun. All is well until there is a stranger at the door. Cassie thinks it's ok to let the stranger into their home but Socute thinks otherwise. There's just something not quite right with the stranger...

Chapter 18

Pat decides to tell Ally they are related. However, things are interrupted by Pat's past catching up with him. Now Brad, Danny, and Seth have to save Pat and Ally from execution.
name: Chapter 18

description:
The Silent Hand of Death

Detective Lieutenant Frank Donavin has made his choice and now he has to live with it. Is The Stalker a hero or a villain? That's the unsettling question Frank has to deal with. A mystery is set in motion as Frank partners with his best friend, Detective Sergeant Michael Devens. They have a clear mission, capture The Stalker...dead or alive!
name: The Silent Hand of Death

description:
The Trap Chp 3

The work crew of Heaven's Gate continue to find a way out of the old Thomas farmhouse, but loose one of their own and find more corpses.
name: The Trap Chp 3

description:
Another Summer

Holy smokes! Joe, Hugo, and Ulysses receive a call from the logging town of Beryl Ridge. However, there's an evil in those woods and all is not what it seems. When everything is backwards, the answers must come to our heroes in the form of a dream. Let's rock!
name: Chapter 7: Another Summer

description:
It's the Urban Myth Investigators! Urban myths investigating OTHER urban myths.

While Earl the Gnome, Steve Sasquatch, and Chupie are enjoying a friendly game of no-limit poker and talking Golden Girls, they're dispatched to Loch Ness for a disturbance that's not what it seems.

The Pink Panther has been entertaining fans of all ages for over 50 years and his antics are back for good! This issue includes four classic tales - The Pink Past, Mountain Pink, Pink Belt, and The Inspector in The Puddle Clue! Enjoy these classic chuckles from the Pink Panther!

1) The Pink Panther - The Pink Past - 5 pages (reprint from The Pink Panther #49 - Mountain Pink)

2) The Pink Panther - Mountain Pink - 7 pages (reprint from The Pink Panther #49 - Mountain Pink)

3) The Inspector - Case of: The Puddle Clue - 5 pages (reprint from The Pink Panther #49 - Mountain Pink)

4) 2) The Pink Panther - Pink Belt - 6 pages (reprint from The Pink Panther #49 - Mountain Pink)
name: The Pink Past

description:
The Pink Panther is on the prowl again! This issue represents four classic Pink Panther stories from the past: Pink Contestant, Pink Ventriloquism, Pink Hostage, and The Inspector in Case of The Cat Burglar! Enjoy these timeless laughs with The Pink Panther and his colorful entourage of characters.

1) The Pink Panther - Pink Contestant - 7 pages (reprint from The Pink Panther #50)

2) The Pink Panther - Pink Ventriloquism - 5 pages (reprint from The Pink Panther #50)

3) The Inspector - Case of: The Cat Burglar - 5 pages (reprint from The Pink Panther #50)

4) 2) The Pink Panther - Pink Hostage - 6 pages (reprint from The Pink Panther #50)

Joe Kubert is one of the great comic book artists. His career literally traverses the history of comics, beginning in 1938 when he became a professional at age 12, to today as one of the greatest draftsmen working in the field. Kubert is known and respected as much for his sinewy, passionate drawing as he is for his consummate storytelling skills. Over his 70-year career in comics, he has worked as an artist, an editor, a publisher, an entrepreneur, and a cartooning auteur. The Art of Joe Kubert is a deluxe, full-color book that honors this legendary creator with beautifully reproduced artwork from every phase of his career as well as critical commentary by the book’s editor, comics historian and Kubert biographer Bill Schelly.
name: HC

description: Aski, the Lucha Libre hero, is back! After surviving a jungle adventure tracking down a dangerous convict, now Aski must step up to protect us from the biggest threat he has faced yet - alien invaders known as The Draconians!

Homecoming

Commander Luce Garaban has returned from a successful military campaign to seize an ancient holy ground in enemy territory. Now he must grapple with the spoils of war: the Black Prism, rumored to be the talisman of an abyssal beast in cryptic lore, and the ill premonitions that come with it.
name: Chapter 1: Homecoming

description: Jax and his band of misfits have wreaked havoc all over the New Mexico territory becoming the most wanted men by the Army. Using ancient Incan technology the men have remained undetected and out of harms way until now. The bandits must travel to Old Mexico and find more technology for a mysterious man who offers then a way to spend their days happy and safe. But what's the catch?
Elflord Reborn takes place twenty years after the conclusion of the last Elflord series. Pangia is a place filled with danger, deceit, and summer blockbuster style action.

Masked

Surreal, Biscuit, and Amber are an unlikely trio of zany cats all trying to escape the grasp of their human captors...will they make it out?
name: Masked

description: Form modest means to the Massachusetts Senate, Elizabeth Warren has proven herself a powerful advocate for the middle class. Her plainspoken approach and dogged attacks on Wall Street have resonated with voters looking for someone who understands the crush of debt and the shackles imposed by student loans. STORM is proud to present this graphic nonfiction portrayal of her rise to power.
Film noir, for kids! A family-friendly detective story filled with mystery, intrigue, and rabbits.
The story of a young aid worker fighting hunger and fear on the frontline.
name: Iraq

description:
The only thing Keira Zeleznovova wants is to be an apprentice at Mage, Inc., but her curmudgeon-y mentor always has one more Intent To Use Magic file to fill out. Through mishaps and trials as an unpaid intern, Keira quickly realizes that there's more paperwork and near death experiences to magic than she could ever imagine. Maybe one day she'll become a powerful mage in her own right.

Collects Chapters 1-6.

Note: The digital edition (4/6/2016) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Leading technology giant R.D.S.L.'s artificial intelligence experiments have gone awry, accidentally giving Sondra, a lowly maintenance robot, a set of human emotions. Now the dangerous automaton has gone rogue and is plunged head first into a world where she doesn't belong.

While the R.D.S.L. security team works to shut her down once and for all, Sondra will have to choose whether to follow her programming or learn what it means to be human while on her mission to meet her maker.

SiRiS Agents Sol and Jelani, trained in the supernatural arts and mystic bounty hunting take rookie agent Khu on her first mission to bring in a maniacal menace. Action, comedy, mystic powers and Water-Wolves come in the debut Motherless Creatures comic!

Now that he's a father, Pewfell is determined to achieve success in his chosen career of wizardry, but somehow it continues to elude him. When his perpetually pesky tenant, Gnoma, is apparently killed in the act of remodeling his house, it looks like a new opportunity might be about to open up for Pewfell in the country...

Take a trip to Planet Urf for a tale of battling barbarian babes, demented robot clerics, devious gnomic real-estate agents, demonically-run corporations, and a slightly slimy, slug-like children's entertainer named Strangeblob Nopants.

This compilation volume collects issue #s 21-24 of the Pewfell comic book series, also available here on ComiXology.
name: Vol. 5

description:
With Eve moving in on Dice's invitation, Eric's life just got a little bit more complicated. Eden doesn't seem to mind though, and with Erin's career on the up and up, things don't seem too bad. But when Alvin and McMahon make their dramatic return, the end can only be near...

A Question of Promise Volume 2 collects issues #9 to #16.
name: Vol. 2

description:
The Silver Surfer delves alone into the furthest depths of the void - tangling with organ-stealing pirates, demonic beasts and a race of alien aristocrats. Everyone's favorite Cosmic Wanderer discovers that even in the midst of a galactic utopia, horror is never far away.

Collects Silver Surfer: In Thy Name #1-4.
name: TPB

description:
HE IS RELENTLESS. HE IS UNSTOPPABLE. HE IS DOOMSDAY.

Superman travels to the nightmare world of Apokolips for a confrontation with Doomsday, the creature who cost the Man of Steel his life. With the help of the mysterious, time-traveling Waverider, Superman at last discovers the shocking truth of his greatest enemy's origin. And just when he thinks the terror is finally over, the murderous juggernaut returns to Earth even more powerful than ever!

DAN JURGENS (SUPERMAN: LOIS & CLARK), JERRY ORDWAY (ADVENTURES OF SUPERMAN) and others pen the sequel to the Earth shattering epic of the Death and Return of Superman by exploring the ramifications of Doomsday's return. Collects DOOMSDAY ANNUAL #1, SUPERMAN: THE DOOMSDAY WARS #1-3, and SUPERMAN/DOOMSDAY: HUNTER/PREY #1-3!
